<br>
While it's true that Russia bore the brunt of the ground fighting in the euro theatre, I think it would be unrealistic to think they could have fought off germany without the second front and especially the naval supression of the german navy (which was almost all from england and america).  It would be hard for russia to get supply if the wolf pack had won.  If you take america out of the equation you very well could get a different outcome to the whole thing.  Could russia afford to send all those tank devisions from the eastern front to help save mosco (sp) if the brittish and american's had not been putting pressure on the japanese?  If mosco (sp) fell, russia would have fallen.  If brit/american air had not supressed the crap out of germany, where would german's jet, v2, and nuclear programs been?  <br>
<br>
In the end it took all the countries (like you've said) to beat a very advanced german war machine but I truely believe it would have been a very bad outcome if america had not joined the fight.<br>
<br>
Anyway, it's interesting to argue about since nobody will ever know what would have happened.<br>
